    1. Participation in the Program
    
    LendSocial manages the Website, which matches you and other persons (each, a "Lender" and, collectively, "Lenders") with a business owner or owners in your or other communities (each, a "Borrower" and, collectively, "Borrowers") in need of affordable capital with added value. In most instances, these Borrowers are considered "high risk" by traditional lenders for a variety of factors, including, but not limited to, the Borrowers' lower average credit scores, the use of the loan proceeds for entrepreneurial endeavors including investment in risky small businesses and in some select cases “start up” businesses, and the state of the economy in many regions. Please carefully review the Website section entitled "Risk and Due Diligence" which highlights the various risks associated with lending online through LendSocial and explains in greater detail the role played by LendSocial.
    By participating in the Program or otherwise accessing or using the Website, you hereby acknowledge and agree that (a) LendSocial makes no representation, warranty, covenant or guarantee that any funds you lend to a Borrower via the Website will be repaid in whole or in part, (b) loans and other similar transactions made via the Website (each, a "Loan") are unsecured and bear a high risk of non-repayment and (c) given your financial situation and objectives, you will lend only those amounts on the Website that you can afford to lose. Loans made via the Website are philanthropic in nature with no offered rate of return and, as such, are not intended as, and cannot be considered as, an investment in a financial instrument or security.
    
    1.1.    Loan Disbursement. You understand that your particular Loans are not made directly by you to the Borrowers and that LendSocial acts as an intermediary between you and the Borrower and will ultimately be the organization to issue the aggregated funding amount.  LendSocial takes sole responsibility in collecting the payments on this Loan.  At no point does issuing a Loan on the Website entitle you to partake in your own collection processes.  LendSocial may voluntarily choose to pre-fund your Borrower in the short-term from its own funds in anticipation of receiving your Loan amounts as backfill. This helps reduce the time the Borrower needs to wait until the Loan is funded on the Website. LendSocial serves as a middle-man in the Loan process and aggregates funds from multiple Lenders via the Website and disburses 100% of these funds on a net billing basis (excluding the interest earned, if any, on such funds while they are held in a LendSocial user loan funds account, which interest is contributed to fund LendSocial's operations) to the Borrowers selected by Lenders for funding on the Website.
    LendSocial is solely responsible for screening and selecting each Borrower (including, without limitation, approving the requests for Loans on the Website) and making all Loan disbursements.  Borrowers are screened through LendSocial’s proprietary credit scoring model and approved for listing if they surpass our qualifications.
    
    1.2    Loan Collection and Repayment. Loans are repaid directly by the Borrower(s) to LendSocial. As Borrowers repay the Loans, LendSocial will credit the accounts of all Lenders on the LendSocial website who have loans outstanding, regardless of whether they supported the particular Borrower successfully repaying. Repayments may be made in periodic installments, depending on the terms of the applicable Loan. These distributions may, in LendSocial's sole discretion, be made periodically or in one lump sum once 100% of all Loan proceeds for a particular Loan have been received by LendSocial. Furthermore, please note that timing of distributions to Lenders of any collected repayment may vary and may be materially impacted because of circumstances that, in LendSocial's judgment, require LendSocial to conduct further reviews with respect to the collected repayments (by way of one example, to resolve issues regarding accuracy of repayment amounts and corresponding data, or for other issues). If, for any reason, LendSocial is unable to collect Loan repayments directly from the Borrowers, repayment of your Loan amounts could be at risk of partial or total delay or non-repayment and a loss of some or all of your principal could occur. While it is the business policy of LendSocial to return 100% of your principal to you over time, you hereby acknowledge and agree that the Borrower(s) will have no direct contractual obligation or liability to pay you any principal and that LendSocial is obligated to repay only such Loan principal to the extent actually received by LendSocial from the Borrowers (subject to the conditions noted above). Neither LendSocial or any Borrower will have any obligation to pay interest on the Loan or other fees or amounts (other than as expressly set forth above) to you. You should note that LendSocial charges an interest to the borrowers on the Loans posted on the Website in order to provide default protection to all our Lenders and cover our expenses.
    
    1.3    Tax Deductibility. You understand that LendSocial is a not a non-profit public benefit corporation. You acknowledge, that because you are making a Loan and not donating any money, you are not eligible to receive a tax deduction. You also understand that you are solely responsible for determining the proper tax treatment for any Loan you make through the Website and the Program. LendSocial has not and will not provide any tax or legal advice to you in connection with any Loan you might make. This Agreement does not attempt to define the tax implications of participating in the Program. If you participate in the Program, you should consult with your own accountants, tax advisors and legal advisors.
    
