    1.8    User Account Inactivity; Instructions for Auto-Donation of Funds to LendSocial or Auto-Withdrawal Return of Funds to User; Potential Escheatment of Funds.
    
    LendSocial welcomes its Users' active participation in the LendSocial Program. However, there may be occasions when a User becomes "inactive" for an extended period of time – i.e., a User does not log in to his or her LendSocial account or there are no credits/withdrawals made to such User's account. Therefore, LendSocial may implement Website features pursuant to which you may instruct LendSocial in advance as to how you wish any remaining balances in your account to be handled in the event your account were to become inactive for a period of 24 or more consecutive months -- namely, whether in such a case of User inactivity, you (i) wish to automatically donate remaining funds in your account to be continuously lent out to Borrowers in LendSocial's Program or (ii) wish for LendSocial to return remaining funds in your account to you via LendSocial's standard account withdrawal process.  In addition, in such cases of User inactivity, LendSocial may elect to automatically terminate the inactive User account.  You will upon registration on the Website automatically be opted-in to instructing LendSocial to auto-convert any remaining account balances as a donation to be continuously lent out to Borrowers using LendSocial's Platform if your account were to become inactive for a period of 24 or more consecutive months. Please note that you are free to change this pre-set option in your discretion and at any time in advance (although you understand any funds that have been auto-donated based on the then-existing preference setting shall not be revocable once the auto-donation has taken place).
    
